    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>Karl Detzer was born September 4, 1891 in Fort Wayne, Indiana. A journalist and free-lance writer, Detzer began his career working for a Fort Wayne newspaper as a reporter and photographer. Following service in World War I, he came to Chicago where wrote advertising copy. He would leave this to write full-time on his own, writing for various pulp magazines, submitting screenplays to Hollywood studios, eventually working as a roving editor for <title render="italic">Reader's Digest</title>. He died April 28, 1987 in Leland, Michigan, where some years earlier he had made his home.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The collections includes biographical and personal materials, correspondence, clippings, articles, motion picture and radio scripts, photographs, and copies of his writings from various magazines.</p>
    </scopecontent>
